Mean \(\pm\) SD contains 2/3 of total number of counts

  • \(\pm\) .
mean_chest <- mean(chest_vec)
sd_chest <- sd(chest_vec)
x_lower <- mean_chest - sd_chest
x_upper <- mean_chest + sd_chest
sd_chest <- chest_vec %>%
  sd
x_lower <- chest_vec %>%
  mean %>%
  `-`(sd_chest)
x_upper <- chest_vec %>%
  mean %>%
  `+`(sd_chest)
hist(chest_vec, 
     breaks = 32.5:48.5, 
     probability = TRUE, 
     main = main_title, 
     sub = sub_title, 
     xlab = x_lab, 
     ylab = y_lab)
abline(v = c(x_lower, x_upper), 
       lty = 2, 
       col = "red")

Comparison with normal curve

  • .
x_chest <- seq(32.5, 48.5, 
               length = 1000)
y_norm <- dnorm(x_chest, 
                mean = mean_chest, 
                sd = sd_chest)
hist(chest_vec, 
     breaks = 32.5:48.5, 
     probability = TRUE, 
     main = main_title, 
     sub = sub_title, 
     xlab = x_lab, 
     ylab = y_lab)

       lty = 2, 
       col = "red")

        density = 20)
